        <h1 class="title">USOMC History</h1>

        <p>
        The United States Open Music Competition (USOMC) was founded in 1992 by a group of music enthusiasts. It is an extremely comprehensive piano competition that both challenges and rewards students of all ages. Over the years, the USOMC has grown from a 500 entry state level competition to a 1000 plus entry national and international level competition. Numerous contestants have traveled from Austria, Hong Kong, Shanghai, and since 2005, from all over China. For the past 15 years, USOMC has created an environment where local, national and international students of all levels have strived to achieve musical excellence.
        </p>

        <p>
